<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-10T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-10T03:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4085: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="#p_FWC1" type="from">Forbes</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-10T17:00:00+09:00">February 10, 1932—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 10—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. The Military Attaché has been informed by the General Staff office
                            that it has been decided that the 9th Division which has been under
                            preparation for departure is to leave for Shanghai. He was further
                            informed that in view of movements of the Chinese fugitive soldiers in
                            the vicinity of Harbin it has been decided that the 2d Division <pb facs="0373" n="269" xml:id="pg_269"/> remain there for the time
                            being until peace and order are restored, the other troops to return to
                            their original stations as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_FWC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>